video.title: Dragons: Race to the Edge
video.synopsis: From the creators of "How to Train Your Dragon" comes a new series that takes Hiccup and Toothless to the edge of adventure.

episodes.synopsis: During their search for the escaped Dagur the Deranged, Hiccup and the Dragon Riders discover a mysterious object -- one that holds their destiny.
episodes.title: Eye of the Beholder, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup and the Dragon Riders journey to Glacier Island to find the Snow Wraith, a fearsome dragon that holds the key to the Dragon Eye's mysteries.
episodes.title: Eye of the Beholder, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: The Dragon Riders discover a lush island that turns out to be the home of the Deathsong, a massive dragon that threatens to trap them forever.
episodes.title: Imperfect Harmony

episodes.synopsis: On an island that will make the perfect outpost, the Dragon Riders discover that the indigenous residents are a mysterious new breed of dragon.
episodes.title: When Darkness Falls

episodes.synopsis: Thinking he's allergic to his dragon, Fishlegs gets hypnotized. He wakes up transformed into an invincible warrior known as Thor Bonecrusher.
episodes.title: Big Man on Berk

episodes.synopsis: When Dagur the Deranged captures Gustav, it's up to Hiccup and the Dragon Riders to get him back.
episodes.title: Gone Gustav Gone

episodes.synopsis: Fireworms invade Dragon's Edge, while Ruffnut and Tuffnut discover that they have an unexpected connection to the island.
episodes.title: Reign of Fireworms

episodes.synopsis: As a Rumblehorn wreaks havoc on Dragon's Edge, Hiccup seeks the help of Stoick, who forms an unexpected bond with the rampaging beast.
episodes.title: Crushing It

episodes.synopsis: Fishlegs and Meatlug liberate the Gronckles from a menacing dragon that has encroached on their ancestral home, Dark Deep.
episodes.title: Quake, Rattle and Roll

episodes.synopsis: The Dragon Riders are surprised to discover who is behind recent attacks on nearby ships -- and to learn exactly what the ships are.
episodes.title: Have Dragon Will Travel, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Heather joins the Dragon Riders, but it's not an easy alliance, especially when Hiccup uncovers a shocking secret about her true identity.
episodes.title: Have Dragon Will Travel, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup and the Dragon Riders rescue a wounded Speed Stinger and take it back to Dragon's Edge, unaware of the dangers that follow.
episodes.title: The Next Big Sting

episodes.synopsis: When Hookfang is drawn to a female Monstrous Nightmare, Snotlout tries to break them up before he loses his friend forever.
episodes.title: Total Nightmare

episodes.synopsis: After an attack on Berk, Astrid trains a crew of backup Dragon Riders to battle back -- but no one can guess how soon the next strike will hit.
episodes.title: Team Astrid

episodes.synopsis: A new enemy named Ryker Grimborn captures Stormfly, sending Hiccup, Toothless and the team off to rescue her before it's too late.
episodes.title: Night of the Hunters, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: As Hiccup and Snotlout race to rescue the others from the Dragon Hunters, they don't realize that someone close to them is working with the enemy.
episodes.title: Night of the Hunters, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: After a strange creature bites Tuffnut, he believes he'll turn into a legendary Lycanwing dragon when the moon is full. Can his friends save him?
episodes.title: Bad Moon Rising

episodes.synopsis: Snotlout and Astrid must deliver a special battle axe to a family wedding, but when an Armorwing dragon derails their plan they have to work together.
episodes.title: Snotlout Gets the Axe

episodes.synopsis: After Hiccup and Toothless heroically save Barf and Belch, the grateful Zippleback tries to repay its life debt by abandoning riders Ruff and Tuff.
episodes.title: The Zippleback Experience

episodes.synopsis: Ryker is determined to create a key to the Dragon Eye, so he heads to Glacier Island to find the Snow Wraith that the Dragon Riders are protecting.
episodes.title: Snow Way Out

episodes.synopsis: When Ruffnut is captured by Dragon Hunters, it's up to Astrid and Tuffnut to defend Dragon's Edge from the invading Dragon Hunter army.
episodes.title: Edge of Disaster, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Unaware of the war on Dragon's Edge, Hiccup, Snotlout and Johann discover an island full of dragons that have been wounded by the Dragon Hunters.
episodes.title: Edge of Disaster, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: When a new dragon is found in Edge Cove, the Dragon Riders must help the Sea Shocker escape a group of hungry Scauldrons.
episodes.title: Shock and Awe

episodes.synopsis: The Skrill returns with a grudge against Hiccup and Toothless, and the Dragon Riders must choose a new course of action to stop the vicious dragon.
episodes.title: A Time to Skrill

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup and Astrid race to stop the Dragon Hunters from tracking the Flightmare after Heather spills secrets from Viggo Grimborn.
episodes.title: Maces and Talons, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: After Heather and the Flightmare have been captured by Viggo and the Dragon Hunters, Hiccup must hatch a plan to outwit the dangerous new enemy.
episodes.title: Maces and Talons, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: While trying to take care of unfinished business, Hiccup and Toothless are lured into a trap. An unlikely rescuer comes to their aid.
episodes.title: Enemy of My Enemy

episodes.synopsis: A wounded Fireworm seeks the Dragon Riders' help in protecting a precious treasure trove against an unfamiliar creature with strange and slimy powers.
episodes.title: Crash Course

episodes.synopsis: When things get out of hand while Fishlegs is left in charge, he seizes another chance to prove he has what it takes to be a leader.
episodes.title: Follow the Leader

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup's and Snotlout's fathers put aside their differences and work with their sons as a team to defend a storehouse against an unusual invader.
episodes.title: Turn and Burn

episodes.synopsis: After Astrid makes an alarming discovery, her life comes to depend on a dragon everyone thought was extinct. Her pals race against time to find it.
episodes.title: Buffalord Soldier

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup reluctantly allows the Dragon Riders to go to a deserted island for a much-needed vacation, but the getaway has an odd effect on their dragons.
episodes.title: A Grim Retreat

episodes.synopsis: After learning that Fishlegs has been secretly communicating with Heather, the gang invites her to the Edge to convince her to join the Dragon Riders.
episodes.title: To Heather or Not to Heather

episodes.synopsis: When Hiccup and Toothless accidentally land in a Dragon Hunter trap, they find themselves the newest contestants in a gladiator-style arena.
episodes.title: Stryke Out

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup and his team rescue a dragon egg and bring it back to the Edge, where it hatches to reveal an ear-splitting surprise!
episodes.title: Tone Death

episodes.synopsis: The gang investigates why Viggo's men are mysteriously shipping marble blocks from a quarry. Next, they try to save two dragons being used as slaves.
episodes.title: Between a Rock and a Hard Place

episodes.synopsis: When Dagur unexpectedly shows up, Hiccup scrambles to prevent him and Heather from discovering each other's presence.
episodes.title: Family on the Edge

episodes.synopsis: Snotlout is sent on an undercover mission to Viggo's dragon auction as part of a plan to rescue the dragons and stop Viggo from getting richer.
episodes.title: Last Auction Heroes

episodes.synopsis: When Viggo offers Hiccup a truce, the wary Dragon Riders investigate and find a potential ally in their fight against the Dragon Hunters.
episodes.title: Defenders of the Wing, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: To prove they're on the same side and pose no threat, the Dragon Riders try to rescue Queen Mala's dragon, which Viggo stole to destroy Dragon's Edge.
episodes.title: Defenders of the Wing: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Tuffnut is eager to impress his visiting cousin, Gruffnut. But Ruffnut is suspicious of his real reasons for coming to Dragon's Edge.
episodes.title: Gruff Around the Edges

episodes.synopsis: The Dragon Riders attend Berk's 400th anniversary celebration, where a bounty on Hiccup's head casts a dark shadow over the festivities.
episodes.title: Midnight Scrum

episodes.synopsis: After getting bad advice from his father, Snotlout tries to seize leadership of the Dragon Riders and starts making reckless decisions on his own.
episodes.title: Not Lout

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup and Heather are shocked to see Dagur among the Dragon Hunters. Snotlout undergoes the Trials, a series of tests he must pass to be Mala's king.
episodes.title: Saving Shattermaster

episodes.synopsis: When a dragon that causes man-eating whirlpools threatens Berk's trade ships, the Dragon Riders must remove it without getting caught in its vortex.
episodes.title: Dire Straits

episodes.synopsis: With his teammates grounded due to lack of sleep from the midnight sun, Hiccup tries to help a hurt dragon alone, but suddenly gets in over his head.
episodes.title: The Longest Day

episodes.synopsis: When Dagur appears at the Edge claiming to know where Viggo keeps his gold, the Dragon Riders fly off to find the stash and return Berk's stolen gold.
episodes.title: Gold Rush

episodes.synopsis: To ensure the future survival of Mala's tribe, she and Hiccup must deposit a newly laid Eruptodon egg into the deadly Grand Volcano so it will hatch.
episodes.title: Out of the Frying Pan

episodes.synopsis: When the twins fly to the Northern Markets to get Tuffnut's mace fixed, a chance turn of events lands them inside a secret Dragon Hunter operation.
episodes.title: Twintuition

episodes.synopsis: While rescuing the dragons from a fire in the stables caused by a powerful lightning storm, Astrid suffers an injury that leaves her blind.
episodes.title: Blindsided

episodes.synopsis: After months of planning, Hiccup launches an operation to capture the Dragon Eye from Viggo, only to find that someone else has beaten them to it.
episodes.title: Shell Shocked: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Although Viggo keeps his promise about the Dragon Eye, Hiccup is unsure whether he can trust him as an ally against Ryker and the Shell Fire dragon.
episodes.title: Shell Shocked: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: While trying to stabilize the volcano that threatens to destroy Dragon's Edge, the Riders discover troubling evidence of new Hunter activity.
episodes.title: Living on the Edge

episodes.synopsis: As the Riders investigate why traders are disappearing from the Northern Markets, Hiccup and Snotlout fall victim to a treasure-hoarding dragon.
episodes.title: Sandbusted

episodes.synopsis: The Riders accept an invite to Berserker Island, where their reunion with Heather, Dagur and a young familiar face is interrupted by a sudden revolt.
episodes.title: Something Rotten on Berserker Island

episodes.synopsis: When Snotlout is rescued from a storm by a tribe of winged women, he thinks he's gone to Valhalla -- until he learns he's going to be their dinner.
episodes.title: Snotlout's Angels

episodes.synopsis: Disobeying Hiccup, the twins follow a retiring Eruptodon to its final resting place, Vanaheim, and learn why no human has ever gone there before.
episodes.title: A Matter of Perspective

episodes.synopsis: When a pair of Outcasts visits the Edge seeking the help of Thor Bonecrusher, Fishlegs allows Snotlout to hypnotize him to evoke his mighty alter ego.
episodes.title: Return of Thor Bonecrusher

episodes.synopsis: After the Edge is ambushed by a group of Singetails, the Riders quickly take flight to ward them off, but are shocked when they get a closer look.
episodes.title: Dawn of Destruction

episodes.synopsis: The Riders flee to Berk, where Stoick's plan for defeating the Flyers, which will require a painful sacrifice, spurs Hiccup to seek an alternative.
episodes.title: The Wings of War, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: An unlikely ally helps Hiccup uncover Singetail behaviors that can be exploited to conquer the Flyers. An overconfident Krogan makes a strategy error.
episodes.title: The Wings of War, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: After Stormfly tangles with two poisonous Slitherwings while defending Garff, Astrid must risk her own life to get an ingredient to make an antidote.
episodes.title: No Dragon Left Behind

episodes.synopsis: When Ruffnut refuses to become Throk's bride because it would mean leaving her twin, Tuffnut fakes his own death to give her the freedom to marry.
episodes.title: Snuffnut

episodes.synopsis: A sketch in an old diary leads Hiccup and Fishlegs back to Vanaheim, where they help Dagur search for his long-missing father, Oswald the Agreeable.
episodes.title: Searching for Oswald ... and Chicken

episodes.synopsis: When Heather goes to meet a man claiming to have seen Oswald, she walks into a trap that forces the Dragon Riders to pay a dear and unexpected price.
episodes.title: Sins of the Past

episodes.synopsis: While hunting for gemstones needed to complete the Dragon Eye 2, Hiccup learns an old friend isn't who he seems. Dagur faces a bully from his past.
episodes.title: In Plain Sight

episodes.synopsis: Stoick and Hiccup are led on a wild goose chase in search of willow bark for medicine, leaving Berk vulnerable to an enemy attack.
episodes.title: No Bark, All Bite

episodes.synopsis: During a trip to Wingmaiden Island to find a Dragon Eye lens, Snotlout challenges Hiccups leadership. On another island, an unlikely romance blooms.
episodes.title: Chain of Command

episodes.synopsis: Upset after learning his ancestors were Hunters who killed off Dramillions, Fishlegs sets out to see if he can find any of the dragon species left.
episodes.title: Loyal Order of Ingerman

episodes.synopsis: Hiccup grows wary when Gruffnut arrives on the twins' 19th birthday to administer a Thorston coming-of-age ritual involving three dangerous challenges.
episodes.title: A Gruff Separation

episodes.synopsis: An announcement leads Astrid to question her relationship with Hiccup. The Riders discover an Armorwing that has a Dragon Eye lens welded to its body.
episodes.title: Mi Amore Wing

episodes.synopsis: While visiting Wingmaiden Island, a baby Razorwhip bonds with Ruffnut, who suddenly finds herself trying her hand at being a Wingmaiden.
episodes.title: Ruff Transition

episodes.synopsis: When the Flyers try to kill him because he's no longer useful, Viggo forces Hiccup to help him get revenge by stealing their Dragon Eye and lenses.
episodes.title: Triple Cross

episodes.synopsis: After learning Krogan is using a Deathsong to lure and subdue Singetails for his growing army of Flyers, the Riders set out to rescue the dragon.
episodes.title: Family Matters

episodes.synopsis: While on night patrol, Stoick is ambushed by the Flyers and gravely injured, leaving Hiccup torn between his duties as a son and as the Riders' leader.
episodes.title: Darkest Night

episodes.synopsis: After learning several Flyers followed Heather to Vanaheim, the Riders must stop them from reporting the sacred island's location to their leader.
episodes.title: Guardians of Vanaheim

episodes.synopsis: With the fifth lens in place, the Dragon Eye 2 unveils the apparent King of Dragons, and Fishlegs immediately knows what it is and where to find it.
episodes.title: King of Dragons, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The Riders race to the home of the true King of Dragons. But the Flyers are already there, and they soon come face to face with the legendary creature.
episodes.title: King of Dragons, Part 2
